      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MEDIA SPIN (1) has returned in good order this prep. Produced a real eye-catcher last start over 1100m at Dubbo, coming from near the tail on the bend to be beaten just over a length. Gets an extra 100m today third-up which looks like the perfect set-up. MEGAPHONE MISS (9) is back after a 20-week spell. Has had plenty of chances in her three preps to date and placed just twice. One of them was here at 1200m so might be worth throwing in the exotics. BAULKHAM HILLS (6) returns from a six-month break for new trainer Michael Lynch. Found a bit of form at the tail end of the maiden prep. Cannot be taken lightly. AZUCAR (2) worked home nicely at Cora last start. Fitter for two runs back from a spell and can play a role despite tackling a better maiden today. The lightly raced ARWA MISS (4) resumes. Showed ability in the maiden prep and is some chance of sneaking into the money.",
